WEBVTT

00:00.023 --> 00:01.639
<i>Previously on "Dominion"... </i>

00:01.664 --> 00:04.968
<i>The added stress of surgery
caused a miscarriage.</i>

00:05.045 --> 00:07.830
[screams]

00:07.856 --> 00:11.008
<i>- What did you do?
- What I had to!</i>

00:11.467 --> 00:13.303
I've been chosen.

00:13.328 --> 00:15.328
These are my markings.

00:15.380 --> 00:18.334
This is the fifth Amphora. Darkness.

00:18.359 --> 00:20.429
It's one of the archangel's weapons.

00:20.455 --> 00:22.372
"And his kingdom was full of darkness,

00:22.397 --> 00:24.847
<i>and they gnawed their
tongues for pain."</i>

00:24.872 --> 00:28.178
If you unlock the Amphora,
it'll wipe us all out,

00:28.203 --> 00:29.691
<i>angels and humans.</i>

00:29.716 --> 00:31.070
<i>I know.</i>

00:31.095 --> 00:34.370
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:34.419 --> 00:37.070
<i>♪
♪</i>

00:37.095 --> 00:39.771
[hisses]

00:40.596 --> 00:48.602
<i>♪
♪</i>

00:50.000 --> 00:56.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:57.132 --> 00:59.907
[electricity crackles]

00:59.932 --> 01:02.316
<i>♪
♪</i>

01:02.341 --> 01:04.462
Oh, no, you're absolutely right.

01:04.488 --> 01:07.107
<i>♪
♪</i>

01:07.132 --> 01:09.506
[electrical buzzing]

01:09.602 --> 01:11.609
What was that?

01:11.634 --> 01:12.833
<i>Find out what's going on... </i>

01:12.858 --> 01:16.516
[nervous chatter]

01:16.541 --> 01:18.125
[gun clicks]

01:18.150 --> 01:20.587
Sanders?

01:21.320 --> 01:23.015
No! [gunshot]

01:23.040 --> 01:24.486
[gasps]

01:24.511 --> 01:27.512
[grunting]

01:27.537 --> 01:30.486
<i>♪
♪</i>

01:30.511 --> 01:31.986
[screams]

01:32.511 --> 01:35.110
[gunfire] [screams]

01:35.135 --> 01:38.587
[overlapping shouts]

01:39.028 --> 01:41.887
[gunshots]

01:42.318 --> 01:44.852
[overlapping shouts]

01:44.920 --> 01:46.708
[both grunting]

01:46.733 --> 01:48.900
[explosion booms]

01:48.925 --> 01:50.287
[screams]

01:50.312 --> 01:51.787
[gunfire]

01:51.812 --> 01:53.359
[explosion booms]

01:53.384 --> 01:54.750
[gunshot]

01:54.775 --> 01:56.725
- Ah!
- [gunfire]

01:56.750 --> 01:58.602
- [grunting]
- Alex!

01:58.659 --> 01:59.602
Help!

01:59.627 --> 02:01.102
Claire!

02:01.127 --> 02:02.301
[both grunting]

02:02.326 --> 02:04.263
[grunting]

02:04.288 --> 02:07.322
Get off me! Get off me!

02:07.347 --> 02:09.714
[grunting]

02:10.097 --> 02:11.897
[gunshot]

02:11.922 --> 02:13.755
[panting]

02:13.780 --> 02:15.359
[background sound fades out]

02:15.384 --> 02:17.452
[heartbeat thumping]

02:17.477 --> 02:21.314
<i>[baby crying in distance]</i>

02:21.339 --> 02:23.455
[background sound returns]

02:23.738 --> 02:24.938
[panting]

02:24.963 --> 02:26.607
Claire, stop!

02:26.632 --> 02:28.715
[overlapping shouting]

02:28.740 --> 02:30.506
Noma, go!

02:30.531 --> 02:32.364
[gunshot]

02:32.389 --> 02:34.859
[alarm blares]

02:34.884 --> 02:36.217
[gunshot ricochets]

02:36.242 --> 02:38.140
[panting]

02:38.165 --> 02:43.107
<i>[baby crying in distance]</i>

02:51.662 --> 02:54.163
<i>[baby crying]</i>

02:54.188 --> 02:57.139
<i>[gentle music]</i>

02:57.183 --> 03:00.222
<i>♪
♪</i>

03:00.261 --> 03:01.760
Hello.

03:01.820 --> 03:05.272
<i>♪
♪</i>

03:05.309 --> 03:08.261
My baby.

03:08.286 --> 03:10.822
My baby.

03:10.847 --> 03:12.931
I thought I lost you.

03:12.944 --> 03:14.076
[baby coos]

03:14.101 --> 03:15.984
It's okay.

03:16.019 --> 03:17.519
It's okay.

03:17.544 --> 03:20.418
Mommy's here. Mommy's here.

03:21.588 --> 03:23.180
<i>Let's go.</i>

03:23.205 --> 03:26.206
<i>[ominous music]</i>

03:26.273 --> 03:29.274
<i>♪
♪</i>

03:29.299 --> 03:30.579
Please don't.

03:30.604 --> 03:32.536
Don't do this, please.

03:32.561 --> 03:34.428
Any... anything... anything you want,

03:34.453 --> 03:36.735
I can get it for you. Please!

03:36.760 --> 03:41.396
David Whele, by order
of the Lady of the City,

03:41.421 --> 03:44.589
you have been sentenced to die.

03:44.614 --> 03:46.801
[whimpers]

03:46.849 --> 03:48.015
[gasps]

03:48.040 --> 03:50.407
Do you have any last words?

03:50.432 --> 03:54.796
Everything I did, I did it for Vega!

03:54.845 --> 03:57.672
[whimpering]

03:57.697 --> 04:01.096
<i>♪
♪</i>

04:01.121 --> 04:02.979
Ah! Ah! Ah!

04:03.004 --> 04:07.995
<i>♪
♪</i>

04:08.020 --> 04:09.536
[metallic thud]

04:09.561 --> 04:11.596
<i>Stay of execution has been granted.</i>

04:11.621 --> 04:14.296
You David Whele?

04:14.956 --> 04:17.308
Your presence has been requested.

04:17.333 --> 04:19.826
What?

04:20.014 --> 04:22.525
Please. What's happening?

04:22.550 --> 04:26.126
Am I free? Has Claire pardoned me?

04:26.151 --> 04:28.012
<i>My sigil.</i>

04:28.037 --> 04:35.851
<i>♪
♪</i>

04:36.289 --> 04:38.219
My lord.

04:38.510 --> 04:40.593
<i>♪
♪</i>

04:40.618 --> 04:43.814
_

04:43.839 --> 04:46.223
<i>♪
♪</i>

04:46.248 --> 04:48.862
Hello, David. Boo!

04:48.887 --> 04:49.916
[gasps]

04:49.941 --> 04:51.515
[laughs]

04:51.540 --> 04:53.916
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:53.941 --> 04:58.506
<i>♪
♪</i>

04:59.546 --> 05:03.746
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
- www.addic7ed.com -

05:04.916 --> 05:06.482
<i>Alex, wait!</i>

05:06.507 --> 05:09.508
- What the hell is this?
- It's the Amphora of Darkness.

05:09.533 --> 05:11.010
Brings out the darkness inside you.

05:11.035 --> 05:12.430
It drives you mad with visions to make you

05:12.455 --> 05:13.704
hurt yourself or someone else.

05:13.729 --> 05:15.416
Some are nightmares but some are dreams,

05:15.441 --> 05:17.575
beautiful but fatal, all end in death.

05:17.600 --> 05:20.773
Well, I'm not seeing
anything, nightmares or dreams.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.507
Well, neither am I but angels
can withstand its effects

05:22.532 --> 05:23.672
longer than humans.

05:23.697 --> 05:25.472
Doesn't explain you though.

05:25.497 --> 05:27.373
- I gotta find Claire.
- No, no! The only way

05:27.398 --> 05:28.884
to help Claire is to find
the Amphora and close it.

05:28.936 --> 05:31.897
No human can do it. Only
an angel can reseal it.

05:31.922 --> 05:34.897
It's close. I can sense it nearby.

05:34.922 --> 05:37.515
I can feel it. Follow me.

05:37.540 --> 05:39.415
Let's go.

05:39.440 --> 05:43.915
[heartbeat thumping]

05:49.011 --> 05:51.538
[door opens]

05:53.970 --> 05:56.256
Claire, what have you done to me?

05:56.336 --> 05:59.287
<i>[ominous music]</i>

05:59.312 --> 06:01.513
<i>♪
♪</i>

06:01.568 --> 06:03.317
Rose?

06:03.342 --> 06:04.724
A female 8-ball.

06:04.842 --> 06:06.959
This is exactly what we needed.

06:06.984 --> 06:10.068
An 8-ball? I'm not an 8-ball.

06:10.093 --> 06:11.559
<i>Claire, what is she talking about?</i>

06:11.584 --> 06:13.046
How does she know my name?

06:13.071 --> 06:16.470
This one's smart. She learns fast.

06:16.495 --> 06:18.578
I'm confident we can break her down,

06:18.603 --> 06:19.753
<i>train her for our purposes.</i>

06:19.778 --> 06:23.112
Train me? You can't be serious.

06:23.137 --> 06:27.096
You're dead. Claire, I shot her, I swear!

06:28.663 --> 06:34.083
Calm yourself, or I'll
remove your black eyes myself.

06:34.108 --> 06:36.597
Rose?

06:37.148 --> 06:40.197
This is too risky.

06:40.312 --> 06:43.198
If we release her to seduce David Whele,

06:43.223 --> 06:44.782
how do we know she won't kill him,

06:44.807 --> 06:46.924
or worse, us?

06:46.949 --> 06:48.572
David needs to be branded a traitor.

06:48.597 --> 06:49.901
It's the perfect plan.

06:49.926 --> 06:52.009
<i>Destroy him or he'll destroy you.</i>

06:52.034 --> 06:54.318
Claire, you must listen to me.

06:54.343 --> 06:55.592
Something is very wrong here.

06:55.617 --> 06:58.059
<i>Please.</i>

06:58.917 --> 07:00.917
Claire.

07:01.516 --> 07:03.686
Claire!

07:04.355 --> 07:06.425
Claire!

07:06.450 --> 07:08.486
Listen to me!

07:08.511 --> 07:10.262
Claire! [door closes]

07:10.287 --> 07:13.288
[heartbeat thumping]

07:15.608 --> 07:18.896
<i>[indistinct shouts in distance]</i>

07:23.699 --> 07:26.985
[grunts]

07:28.005 --> 07:30.840
<i>[footsteps approaching]</i>

07:32.077 --> 07:33.827
<i>[shouting in distance]</i>

07:34.027 --> 07:35.821
Okay.

07:35.846 --> 07:38.141
[yelps] Ah!

07:39.734 --> 07:42.546
[straining]

07:47.354 --> 07:51.856
Well, if it isn't my dear old acolyte.

07:52.203 --> 07:54.503
Been a long time, William.

07:54.672 --> 07:58.128
Gabriel?

07:58.153 --> 08:00.548
Are you the one that brought me here?

08:00.573 --> 08:01.772
Where am I?

08:01.797 --> 08:03.182
<i>Don't you recognize it?</i>

08:03.207 --> 08:05.457
[laughs]

08:05.584 --> 08:08.552
The desert heat must have been brutal.

08:08.577 --> 08:10.831
You took shelter here with your gun

08:10.862 --> 08:13.279
<i>and its six little bullets.</i>

08:13.331 --> 08:14.997
<i>Poor boy, thought you had escaped.</i>

08:15.033 --> 08:16.500
<i>Welcome back.</i>

08:16.535 --> 08:18.302
I don't know what you're talking about.

08:19.261 --> 08:22.562
- And I'm not afraid of you.
- <i>That so?</i>

08:22.587 --> 08:25.755
This tough exterior of
yours is just a facade.

08:25.780 --> 08:27.613
<i>I know the real you.</i>

08:27.638 --> 08:31.024
Sniveling coward that
served me all those years.

08:31.049 --> 08:35.177
- No, I...
- [stammers]

08:35.202 --> 08:37.751
I'm not the same William anymore.

08:37.775 --> 08:42.407
I was chosen by God... our Father.

08:42.432 --> 08:45.547
Come now. It's embarrassing.

08:45.572 --> 08:48.585
You? The Chosen One?

08:48.610 --> 08:50.951
I am the Chosen One.

08:50.986 --> 08:54.551
I-I have the scars to prove it.

08:54.576 --> 08:57.217
Gabriel, I was tested in the desert,

08:57.242 --> 09:00.794
and I was saved by the grace of God.

09:00.829 --> 09:04.965
When everyone else
deserted me, He never did.

09:06.829 --> 09:09.437
- [grunts]
- God is gone!

09:09.462 --> 09:11.295
He left you too.

09:11.440 --> 09:13.273
You're not the Chosen One.

09:13.298 --> 09:15.098
You're a reject!

09:15.133 --> 09:16.766
Ah!

09:16.802 --> 09:19.996
[groans]

09:20.021 --> 09:22.696
Gabriel!

09:23.688 --> 09:25.305
[gunfire]

09:25.330 --> 09:29.196
[screams]

09:29.221 --> 09:32.222
[gunfire]

09:38.283 --> 09:40.283
<i>We'll need to search all the floors.</i>

09:40.308 --> 09:42.892
How the hell did the
Amphora get inside the city?

09:42.917 --> 09:44.333
I don't know,

09:44.358 --> 09:48.014
but obviously Julian must
have found it in New Delphi.

09:48.039 --> 09:49.173
[distant screaming]

09:49.198 --> 09:51.165
Quit it.

09:51.190 --> 09:52.836
I'm not seeing any visions or whatever.

09:52.861 --> 09:53.803
But you're human.

09:53.839 --> 09:55.007
You should have been affected by now.

09:55.032 --> 09:56.339
Perhaps he won't be.

09:56.425 --> 09:58.258
The Amphora brings out the darkness within,

09:58.283 --> 09:59.757
but Alex is the last pure heart.

09:59.782 --> 10:00.677
Meaning?

10:00.729 --> 10:03.082
Maybe there's no darkness inside you.

10:03.384 --> 10:05.000
[grunts]

10:05.025 --> 10:07.282
Help me.

10:09.237 --> 10:10.436
<i>We need to split up.</i>

10:10.489 --> 10:12.593
The Amphora's designed to preserve itself.

10:12.618 --> 10:14.190
It'll choose a victim to protect it.

10:14.242 --> 10:15.358
<i>We need to hurry.</i>

10:15.360 --> 10:17.782
He may not succumb, but you and I will.

10:18.198 --> 10:19.320
I'll search up here.

10:19.345 --> 10:21.679
I'll take this floor.

10:42.027 --> 10:46.980
♪ Hush, little baby, don't say a word ♪

10:47.142 --> 10:50.343
♪ Mama's gonna buy you a mockingbird ♪

10:50.458 --> 10:53.792
♪ And if that mockingbird don't sing ♪

10:53.817 --> 10:57.201
♪ Mama's gonna buy you a diamond ring ♪

10:57.226 --> 10:59.491
Yes. Yes.

10:59.516 --> 11:02.884
How are my girls?

11:02.909 --> 11:04.601
<i>Come here.</i>

11:04.626 --> 11:07.292
Hard to believe

11:07.317 --> 11:10.868
this is our life sometimes, isn't it?

11:10.996 --> 11:13.963
[baby coos]

11:15.690 --> 11:18.141
You have no idea.

11:28.113 --> 11:29.948
Alex?

11:31.524 --> 11:33.246
What is it?

11:33.271 --> 11:35.271
You can't see that?

11:36.786 --> 11:38.613
See what?

11:52.588 --> 11:56.257
[breathing heavily]

11:56.282 --> 11:59.250
[distant screaming and gunfire]

12:17.670 --> 12:20.217
[exhales]

12:32.155 --> 12:35.740
Damn it. There's nothing in there either.

12:35.765 --> 12:37.865
What is it?

12:38.938 --> 12:40.103
Nothing.

12:40.139 --> 12:41.138
Come on.

12:41.190 --> 12:43.857
We need to find the
Amphora, end this thing.

12:49.799 --> 12:51.599
Alex?

12:51.650 --> 12:53.033
We should split up.

12:53.068 --> 12:55.021
No, we already split from Michael.

12:55.046 --> 12:56.546
It's too dangerous. We
need to stick together.

12:56.548 --> 12:59.468
I'm a soldier. I can handle myself.

12:59.493 --> 13:01.743
I'll be fine, I swear.

13:01.970 --> 13:03.789
Okay. Just be careful.

13:03.814 --> 13:04.880
Yeah.

13:23.125 --> 13:24.490
Ah.

13:26.605 --> 13:27.937
<i>What is this?</i>

13:27.962 --> 13:31.351
Is this some kind of a trick?

13:31.376 --> 13:33.802
You're...

13:33.854 --> 13:35.103
me.

13:35.138 --> 13:37.138
Well, now you're just stating the obvious.

13:37.163 --> 13:41.312
It's time you and I had a little
conversation about our destiny.

13:41.337 --> 13:42.719
Our destiny?

13:45.699 --> 13:49.284
These are dark times, David.

13:49.319 --> 13:50.985
<i>And they grow darker.</i>

13:51.037 --> 13:53.607
<i>But there's a bright
future ahead of you.</i>

13:53.632 --> 13:55.123
Or there can be.

13:55.158 --> 13:56.574
It's up to you.

13:56.586 --> 14:00.889
You could be Lord of the City.

14:00.914 --> 14:03.381
You play your cards right,

14:03.416 --> 14:07.418
you can have one of these too.

14:07.471 --> 14:09.888
No. No.

14:09.923 --> 14:11.473
Look at you.

14:11.508 --> 14:13.918
You're not a lord. You're an eight-ball.

14:13.943 --> 14:16.404
Hey, I'm a survivor.

14:16.429 --> 14:19.814
The end of the day,
that's all that matters.

14:19.850 --> 14:22.817
But you...

14:22.853 --> 14:25.153
you're holding me back.

14:25.188 --> 14:27.210
What do you want from me?

14:27.235 --> 14:31.056
Let it go. Embrace who you've become.

14:31.191 --> 14:33.691
Renounce your...

14:33.877 --> 14:36.391
humanity or whatever you call it.

14:36.416 --> 14:38.950
And become a monster like you.

14:39.002 --> 14:40.874
Bow down to the angels.

14:40.899 --> 14:42.337
Never.

14:42.372 --> 14:45.461
You can take my life,
but my soul is my own,

14:45.486 --> 14:47.486
something you will never understand.

14:47.521 --> 14:51.285
Souls, David, really?

14:55.290 --> 14:56.778
Don't touch those.

14:56.830 --> 15:00.781
Each of these items represents
the soul of a man or woman

15:00.806 --> 15:04.169
you destroyed on your way to power.

15:04.204 --> 15:07.707
And you kept them in a trophy case.

15:10.048 --> 15:13.147
Let's be honest, David.

15:13.502 --> 15:16.608
You've been a monster like me

15:16.633 --> 15:20.047
longer than you'd like to admit.

15:25.894 --> 15:28.728
Still stubborn, I see.

15:28.789 --> 15:30.906
Maybe this will help.

15:34.419 --> 15:37.582
That's private. Where did you get that?

15:39.369 --> 15:42.935
They have a strange
desire for certain items.

15:42.960 --> 15:44.052
Who is she?

15:44.077 --> 15:46.077
Arika's mother.

15:46.102 --> 15:47.652
You remind me of her.

15:47.677 --> 15:50.332
That's mine. Give it back.

15:50.357 --> 15:52.298
[grunts]

15:57.227 --> 16:00.095
I don't want people to see her that way.

16:00.144 --> 16:02.844
Claire, please.

16:02.873 --> 16:05.457
[sobs]

16:05.482 --> 16:09.037
Now, are you ready to obey?

16:09.916 --> 16:12.232
Uh-huh.

16:20.796 --> 16:22.963
<i>Michael.</i>

16:22.988 --> 16:24.927
Michael.

16:24.952 --> 16:27.953
[choking]

16:33.415 --> 16:35.409
[flashlight clatters]

16:37.818 --> 16:40.507
No!

16:50.394 --> 16:51.969
Oops.

16:54.011 --> 16:56.261
<i>[solemn music]</i>

16:56.286 --> 16:58.089
<i>Noma... </i>

16:58.932 --> 17:00.682
what have you done?

17:00.734 --> 17:02.817
I'm ending this war.

17:02.853 --> 17:05.722
Something I should have done 25 years ago.

17:07.082 --> 17:09.249
Alex had to die.

17:09.396 --> 17:12.347
Father's markings are gone forever.

17:12.579 --> 17:14.931
Now, so is he.

17:14.955 --> 17:17.115
It's over, Michael.

17:17.140 --> 17:19.432
You failed.

17:19.457 --> 17:22.207
<i>[screaming]</i>

17:22.232 --> 17:24.510
[screams]

17:24.535 --> 17:26.734
Hear that, Michael?

17:27.019 --> 17:28.425
It's the end.

17:28.462 --> 17:31.129
The death of all God's creations.

17:31.154 --> 17:34.409
[screams]

17:37.448 --> 17:40.449
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:40.474 --> 17:46.311
<i>♪
♪</i>

17:46.336 --> 17:48.776
Noma.

18:10.087 --> 18:12.197
[screams]

18:26.799 --> 18:29.757
[grunting]

18:34.528 --> 18:37.112
No. No.

18:37.164 --> 18:39.697
[screeching]

18:39.722 --> 18:42.534
I missed you, baby. Mmm.

18:42.586 --> 18:45.870
Claire! What happened to you?

18:45.895 --> 18:48.540
That's no way to talk to your wife.

18:48.565 --> 18:50.153
What's wrong?

18:50.178 --> 18:53.105
Don't you think I'm pretty anymore?

18:53.130 --> 18:54.906
That's not what I meant.

18:54.931 --> 18:57.382
Because I want you, William.

18:57.434 --> 19:01.519
Mmm!

19:01.555 --> 19:04.740
This is another test from God for me.

19:04.765 --> 19:09.121
[laughing]

19:09.146 --> 19:12.523
You actually believe that shit?

19:12.548 --> 19:15.081
Well, I have news for you.

19:15.368 --> 19:17.035
You're a false prophet.

19:17.070 --> 19:18.620
You're wrong.

19:18.655 --> 19:20.455
I've transformed, changed.

19:20.490 --> 19:23.208
Shh! Stop!

19:23.243 --> 19:25.210
That blinding flash of light

19:25.245 --> 19:27.128
that saved you from the thieves?

19:27.164 --> 19:29.998
That wasn't a gift from God.

19:30.050 --> 19:32.854
That was the thief's gun backfiring on him.

19:32.879 --> 19:36.087
Mmm! It killed him.

19:36.089 --> 19:38.552
Dead, dead, dead.

19:38.577 --> 19:43.338
While you... you were
cowering in the corner.

19:43.562 --> 19:45.979
My William.

19:46.004 --> 19:47.209
<i>That's not true.</i>

19:47.234 --> 19:50.079
I heard the voice of God, and he...

19:50.104 --> 19:51.319
Aah!

19:51.354 --> 19:54.272
[laughing]

19:54.324 --> 19:58.109
That was your voice. You
were talking to yourself.

19:58.161 --> 20:01.329
Mm-hmm.

20:01.364 --> 20:03.498
See all this?

20:07.222 --> 20:09.223
This is what really happened.

20:09.248 --> 20:11.789
<i>You were a prisoner
to a pack of 8-balls.</i>

20:11.814 --> 20:13.850
<i>They fed you rats.</i>

20:13.875 --> 20:16.258
They did...

20:16.283 --> 20:18.940
unspeakable things to you.

20:18.965 --> 20:21.015
And it was fun.

20:21.051 --> 20:23.572
No miracles.

20:23.597 --> 20:28.017
Just you... and your stupid mind

20:28.042 --> 20:30.582
justifying the disgusting things

20:30.607 --> 20:32.560
that happened to you.

20:32.612 --> 20:37.371
Oh! I see you miss me too, William.

20:39.748 --> 20:42.833
But you're no chosen one.

20:42.858 --> 20:44.572
No.

20:44.597 --> 20:46.463
You're nothing.

20:46.488 --> 20:50.646
You're delusional, weak.

20:51.005 --> 20:54.340
You always were.

20:54.365 --> 20:56.767
Who could ever love you?

21:30.406 --> 21:33.063
You're safe now.

21:54.603 --> 21:57.429
Do we have any reason to fear you?

21:57.454 --> 21:59.489
No.

21:59.532 --> 22:01.532
Good girl.

22:07.228 --> 22:08.761
[whimpers]

22:08.813 --> 22:11.127
Your mother was a lunatic.

22:11.152 --> 22:14.820
She was diagnosed as
bipolar when you very young.

22:14.845 --> 22:17.646
She saw things that weren't there.

22:17.778 --> 22:19.144
She needed help.

22:19.169 --> 22:21.443
But she didn't want it. She hurt you.

22:21.468 --> 22:23.342
She didn't know what she was doing.

22:23.367 --> 22:24.912
You thought she was a monster.

22:24.937 --> 22:27.449
No, I loved my mother.

22:27.474 --> 22:29.342
You're afraid of her.

22:29.367 --> 22:32.850
Afraid of becoming her.

22:33.124 --> 22:36.483
Now... recite your lines.

22:36.508 --> 22:39.150
No.

22:49.276 --> 22:54.081
I said... recite your lines.

22:56.576 --> 23:00.462
I don't want to fight anymore, David.

23:00.487 --> 23:03.510
Don't treat me like this.

23:03.535 --> 23:06.680
Good. You're ready.

23:06.886 --> 23:09.832
Now strip.

23:16.446 --> 23:20.614
I'm offering you everything
you've ever wanted.

23:20.639 --> 23:24.785
Yes. Lord of the City, but not like this.

23:24.810 --> 23:28.061
- You're inhuman.
- So are you.

23:28.113 --> 23:32.130
You killed innocents. You
tried to assassinate Claire.

23:32.155 --> 23:34.145
You conned Zoe into a war.

23:34.170 --> 23:36.921
You left your own son in the desert to die.

23:36.956 --> 23:38.506
I had to.

23:38.541 --> 23:41.498
Those things I did in order to survive.

23:41.544 --> 23:44.045
Unh! Oh!

23:44.097 --> 23:46.464
Let's be blood brothers.

23:46.516 --> 23:48.966
I was a husband, a father.

23:49.018 --> 23:51.944
I had a family! I loved them dearly.

23:51.969 --> 23:53.552
I lost it all!

23:53.773 --> 23:56.023
Tell me, how does that make me inhuman?

23:56.059 --> 23:57.808
Yes, you loved them,

23:57.860 --> 24:00.895
and when they were taken, it changed you.

24:00.947 --> 24:05.057
[whimpers]

24:05.082 --> 24:08.467
<i>Woman: David.</i>

24:08.492 --> 24:11.710
Help us, Daddy.

24:11.735 --> 24:16.154
Charles? Peggy?

24:16.179 --> 24:17.523
Eleanor!

24:17.548 --> 24:19.748
[snarling]

24:21.842 --> 24:24.042
Love is a liability, a distraction.

24:24.067 --> 24:25.780
It's what's been holding you back.

24:25.805 --> 24:27.722
That's why you pushed William away.

24:27.747 --> 24:30.790
No, it was his crying that lead them

24:30.815 --> 24:32.932
to where we were hiding.

24:32.957 --> 24:34.634
It was his fault that they died.

24:34.659 --> 24:37.834
Now was it?

24:37.859 --> 24:40.834
Aah!

24:42.319 --> 24:45.571
[groaning]

24:53.077 --> 24:57.129
The war was the best thing
that ever happened to you

24:57.154 --> 25:01.740
because it made you the
man you were meant to be.

25:02.041 --> 25:04.417
Me.

25:08.852 --> 25:11.353
You love your Daddy, huh?

25:11.378 --> 25:12.601
She can't stop watching you.

25:12.626 --> 25:14.592
So cute. Such a big girl.

25:14.617 --> 25:15.695
You hungry?

25:15.720 --> 25:18.874
Maybe Daddy could get you something.

25:18.899 --> 25:22.295
I'll get her bottle.

25:22.894 --> 25:24.338
[glasses clinking]

25:24.363 --> 25:27.070
Hey. Is Daddy gonna feed you?

25:27.095 --> 25:28.594
Hmm?

25:34.420 --> 25:39.306
What is it? Is it too hot?

25:39.709 --> 25:43.125
No, it's... it's nothing.

25:53.448 --> 25:58.818
Alex... where'd the crib go?

25:59.315 --> 26:01.187
What crib?

26:05.995 --> 26:08.496
We have to get out of here.

26:08.521 --> 26:10.187
You have to trust me. We have to...

26:10.212 --> 26:12.429
We have to get out of here now.

26:12.454 --> 26:14.293
Alex, listen to me. We have to...

26:14.318 --> 26:16.287
- [Willow crying]
- I'm seeing...

26:16.320 --> 26:17.638
Just... just wait.

26:17.663 --> 26:21.179
It's okay. It's okay, sweetie.

26:21.204 --> 26:23.362
Alex, I...

26:23.707 --> 26:26.241
Alex?

26:26.266 --> 26:27.265
[Willow continues crying]

26:27.290 --> 26:29.063
Alex?

26:29.088 --> 26:32.063
[crying stops]

26:35.456 --> 26:38.741
Willow? Alex?

26:38.766 --> 26:41.844
W-where's Willow?

26:41.869 --> 26:45.537
[sobbing]

26:45.562 --> 26:48.294
No!

26:56.311 --> 26:57.810
Wait. Where are you going?

26:57.835 --> 26:59.118
Outside. Come on.

26:59.170 --> 27:00.144
But I thought you said

27:00.169 --> 27:01.418
you could sense the Amphora in here.

27:01.443 --> 27:02.961
Maybe I was wrong.

27:02.986 --> 27:04.467
Ah!

27:04.492 --> 27:06.860
Put it down.

27:09.117 --> 27:10.416
What are you doing?

27:10.441 --> 27:11.440
Something's wrong with you.

27:11.475 --> 27:13.339
Something's off.

27:13.364 --> 27:16.565
Unh!

27:16.701 --> 27:18.669
Get away from him!

27:19.808 --> 27:21.846
I trusted you.

27:21.871 --> 27:23.712
That day, you said you'd
protect him with your life,

27:23.737 --> 27:24.681
but you've been waiting for a chance

27:24.706 --> 27:25.605
to kill him, haven't you?

27:25.630 --> 27:27.256
No! Archangel, no, I promised you.

27:27.281 --> 27:28.870
Lies! I know what's in your heart.

27:28.895 --> 27:29.909
Back off, Michael.

27:29.934 --> 27:30.784
You don't know what you're saying.

27:30.809 --> 27:31.691
It's the Darkness talking.

27:31.716 --> 27:33.487
You don't know her, Alex.
She's hiding something.

27:34.121 --> 27:36.682
Get back! You can't have it!

27:36.707 --> 27:38.042
Wait, what are you talking about?

27:38.067 --> 27:40.853
The Amphora. She has the Amphora.

27:40.878 --> 27:42.460
Stay here.

27:42.485 --> 27:44.402
I think I know where she hid it.

27:44.427 --> 27:47.859
Alex. Alex, get back here!

27:57.173 --> 28:00.156
Alex, stop!

28:02.760 --> 28:06.045
- Tell me the truth, Michael.
- Alex.

28:06.070 --> 28:08.404
All you care about...

28:08.439 --> 28:10.773
are my markings.

28:10.825 --> 28:13.275
<i>I don't mean anything to you.</i>

28:13.327 --> 28:14.994
Is it true?

28:15.029 --> 28:16.311
No, of course not.

28:16.336 --> 28:17.807
These are all you care about!

28:17.832 --> 28:20.082
Only at first.

28:20.414 --> 28:23.624
You were just a tiny infant.

28:23.861 --> 28:26.756
How could so helpless a
creature bring my father back?

28:26.781 --> 28:30.983
So, for a time, yes,

28:31.008 --> 28:34.728
the markings were all I cared for.

28:35.031 --> 28:38.916
But as the boy who would carry them grew,

28:38.941 --> 28:44.195
I saw that he was good and kind and brave.

28:44.849 --> 28:48.615
No father could be prouder of any son.

28:52.069 --> 28:54.236
It's not enough, Michael.

28:54.261 --> 28:56.449
- [gunshot]
- [gasps]

28:57.947 --> 29:01.366
[crying]

29:03.427 --> 29:06.395
<i>[solemn music]</i>

29:06.420 --> 29:11.043
<i>♪
♪</i>

29:11.068 --> 29:14.460
[screams]

29:17.368 --> 29:20.069
What are you holding on to, David?

29:20.144 --> 29:23.197
There's no one left to
fight for except yourself.

29:23.222 --> 29:26.315
Survive.

29:26.350 --> 29:30.102
Your humanity is hanging by a thread.

29:30.131 --> 29:32.465
Cut it.

29:32.490 --> 29:34.940
Bow down to me.

29:34.992 --> 29:40.863
All the horrible things I've done...

29:40.915 --> 29:44.199
You're right...

29:44.251 --> 29:45.751
about me.

29:45.786 --> 29:48.837
About everything.

29:48.873 --> 29:51.457
[crying]

29:51.482 --> 29:53.448
Very good.

29:57.632 --> 29:59.431
[grunts]

29:59.467 --> 30:01.884
[screaming]

30:05.389 --> 30:08.557
<i>[crying]</i>

30:13.216 --> 30:15.374
Get up.

30:15.399 --> 30:17.116
<i>Alex?</i>

30:17.151 --> 30:19.201
What are you doing here?

30:19.236 --> 30:23.322
You've been spreading lies, William.

30:23.324 --> 30:24.873
What lies?

30:24.909 --> 30:27.826
Tell me, who am I?

30:27.878 --> 30:29.795
You're Alex.

30:29.820 --> 30:32.121
[grunts]

30:33.126 --> 30:36.106
<i>Who am I?</i>

30:37.685 --> 30:38.987
Who am I, William?

30:39.012 --> 30:40.673
Why are you doing this?

30:40.725 --> 30:43.704
Yeah, there's an easy answer.

30:44.005 --> 30:46.361
You see these?

30:46.386 --> 30:48.986
These are my markings,

30:49.011 --> 30:52.056
so let me ask you again.

30:53.737 --> 30:55.370
Who am I?

30:55.719 --> 30:57.352
Don't make me say it.

30:57.377 --> 30:59.243
- [gunshot]
- Who am I?

30:59.276 --> 31:00.888
You're... you're... you're the Chosen One.

31:00.913 --> 31:02.413
Who am I?

31:02.438 --> 31:03.732
You're the Chosen One!

31:03.757 --> 31:06.467
That's right!

31:06.877 --> 31:09.604
And you're not.

31:09.915 --> 31:12.966
Your scars are just...

31:12.991 --> 31:15.459
deformities.

31:15.484 --> 31:19.403
They mean nothing.

31:19.574 --> 31:23.533
You mean nothing.

31:24.185 --> 31:28.739
Your marriage to Claire means nothing.

31:36.528 --> 31:39.999
[breathing heavily]

31:42.208 --> 31:43.394
No.

31:43.419 --> 31:44.702
[sobs]

31:44.727 --> 31:47.198
<i>My markings... </i>

31:47.223 --> 31:49.316
<i>my markings are gone.</i>

31:49.341 --> 31:51.999
You know what to do.

31:54.074 --> 31:56.491
[sobbing]

32:02.417 --> 32:06.371
I don't want to fight anymore, David.

32:08.124 --> 32:09.673
Hello?

32:09.698 --> 32:12.009
David?

32:16.372 --> 32:20.324
Seducing David was
never the mission, Arika.

32:20.349 --> 32:22.048
Killing you was.

32:22.073 --> 32:25.658
Oh, please.

32:25.683 --> 32:27.683
Don't do this.

32:27.708 --> 32:28.843
Look at you.

32:28.868 --> 32:33.780
Helpless, crazy.

32:36.444 --> 32:38.257
Like mother, like daughter.

32:38.282 --> 32:41.187
No, I'm not her.

32:45.061 --> 32:48.387
[screams]

32:50.817 --> 32:53.284
Please.

32:53.309 --> 32:57.599
I-I did everything you asked of me.

32:57.945 --> 33:00.195
Have mercy.

33:00.220 --> 33:05.278
You never showed me mercy, so why should I?

33:07.533 --> 33:10.013
Get on your knees.

33:10.818 --> 33:13.018
Rose...

33:13.043 --> 33:16.013
what I did, killing you,

33:16.038 --> 33:18.881
it was so wrong.

33:18.906 --> 33:22.074
I am so sorry.

33:22.099 --> 33:26.101
Please forgive me.

33:26.126 --> 33:28.062
Forgive me.

33:28.087 --> 33:31.361
[soft thud]

33:38.002 --> 33:40.415
Stop.

33:42.648 --> 33:45.963
<i>Are you going to kill me again?</i>

33:56.237 --> 33:58.938
<i>[door closes]</i>

34:00.703 --> 34:02.953
[intermittent screams]

34:02.997 --> 34:07.411
Help me!

34:29.880 --> 34:30.880
Nomes?

34:30.931 --> 34:32.181
Stop!

34:32.206 --> 34:33.327
Don't come any closer!

34:33.351 --> 34:34.301
<i>Get back!</i>

34:34.326 --> 34:36.664
Okay, okay.

34:37.188 --> 34:39.103
We need to close the Amphora.

34:39.129 --> 34:41.036
<i>It lies.</i>

34:41.061 --> 34:43.859
Whatever it's telling you, it's not real.

34:43.884 --> 34:45.667
They are real.

34:45.692 --> 34:46.725
I can see them.

34:46.804 --> 34:48.907
I won't let you take them away again.

34:48.931 --> 34:51.065
Take what away?

34:51.091 --> 34:53.289
<i>Noma.</i>

34:53.313 --> 34:54.928
Get back!

34:54.953 --> 34:57.188
Noma, you're gonna fall.

34:57.213 --> 34:58.512
I won't.

34:58.537 --> 35:00.003
I can fly.

35:00.028 --> 35:02.028
You can't! It's the Darkness.

35:02.053 --> 35:03.712
It's tricking you.

35:03.737 --> 35:06.789
<i>Your wings aren't back.</i>

35:08.403 --> 35:11.888
Get back, or I'll fly away with it.

35:11.913 --> 35:15.047
If you jump, you'll die.

35:15.072 --> 35:17.740
I gave them up once.

35:17.765 --> 35:20.933
I did it for you, Alex.

35:20.958 --> 35:24.126
I won't do it again.

35:24.151 --> 35:27.490
I need them to go home again.

35:29.390 --> 35:32.572
How else will I fly back to Heaven?

35:34.401 --> 35:35.945
They're a part of me.

35:35.970 --> 35:38.603
And you're a part of me.

35:39.629 --> 35:43.177
Please don't do this!

35:44.353 --> 35:47.350
I need you.

35:48.811 --> 35:52.834
You're my Nomes forever.

35:54.183 --> 35:56.850
I need you.

35:56.875 --> 35:59.493
Come to me.

36:01.816 --> 36:04.650
[gasps]

36:04.675 --> 36:06.531
Alex?

36:07.676 --> 36:09.042
Alex?

36:09.067 --> 36:12.947
[screams]

36:12.972 --> 36:14.354
I got you.

36:14.379 --> 36:16.440
I'm here. I'm here.

36:16.465 --> 36:19.166
I got you.

36:19.394 --> 36:20.706
Noma,

36:20.731 --> 36:23.140
I can't close this,

36:23.165 --> 36:25.544
and Michael is too far gone.

36:25.569 --> 36:27.940
You can do this, Noma.

36:28.152 --> 36:29.953
Alex, get away from her!

36:29.978 --> 36:31.086
Michael, no!

36:31.111 --> 36:33.445
[grunts]

36:33.470 --> 36:35.721
Stop! Stop! Stop!

36:35.746 --> 36:37.822
It's the Darkness!

36:40.500 --> 36:42.102
Stop! Stop!

36:43.799 --> 36:46.139
[grunts]

36:49.226 --> 36:50.843
<i>Michael!</i>

36:50.868 --> 36:52.935
Michael, no!

36:52.960 --> 36:56.578
Get back, Alex! She wants you dead.

36:56.603 --> 36:58.720
[groans]

36:58.745 --> 37:01.085
<i>Michael, please, it's not real!</i>

37:01.110 --> 37:02.741
- It's the Darkness!
- It's not real!

37:02.766 --> 37:05.183
None of it's real! We
need to close the Amphora!

37:05.218 --> 37:06.994
I should've done this long ago.

37:07.019 --> 37:09.695
Get on your knees.

37:09.720 --> 37:11.709
[grunts]

37:11.734 --> 37:14.408
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

37:14.433 --> 37:18.101
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:18.376 --> 37:20.710
<i>[chorus singing]</i>

37:20.735 --> 37:28.741
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:39.002 --> 37:42.337
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:42.389 --> 37:50.395
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:52.394 --> 37:55.120
How did you do that?

37:56.811 --> 37:59.111
[gasps]

37:59.136 --> 38:01.719
[whimpers]

38:01.744 --> 38:04.378
I'm so sorry.

38:04.806 --> 38:07.057
Your wings.

38:07.082 --> 38:10.500
I'm so sorry.

38:10.525 --> 38:13.076
[crying]

38:13.101 --> 38:21.407
<i>♪
♪</i>

38:21.432 --> 38:24.399
<i>[dramatic alternative music]</i>

38:24.424 --> 38:32.672
<i>♪
♪</i>

38:56.861 --> 38:58.413
What have I done?

38:58.465 --> 39:01.749
<i>♪
♪</i>

39:01.801 --> 39:05.086
[screaming]

39:07.013 --> 39:10.446
[choking]

39:12.813 --> 39:20.830
<i>♪
♪</i>

39:35.085 --> 39:38.306
[sobbing]

39:40.256 --> 39:48.262
<i>♪
♪</i>

40:48.682 --> 40:51.420
I will kill them.

40:53.446 --> 40:55.620
I will kill them all.

40:56.562 --> 40:59.219
[sobbing]

40:59.244 --> 41:07.634
<i>♪
♪</i>

41:12.160 --> 41:15.798
The Amphora of Darkness has
served my kind for an eternity,

41:15.823 --> 41:18.941
<i>but now I realize it should've
been destroyed long ago.</i>

41:18.966 --> 41:22.159
We need to find out who survived.

41:22.291 --> 41:25.304
Come on.

41:28.536 --> 41:29.868
Be careful.

41:29.893 --> 41:31.726
Whoever did this will still be near.

41:31.751 --> 41:39.757
<i>♪
♪</i>

42:06.050 --> 42:10.169
Well, that was rather quick.

42:10.252 --> 42:12.786
No matter.

42:12.819 --> 42:14.836
It's time.

